.TH "pmcraid_allocate_control_blocks" 9 "pmcraid_allocate_control_blocks" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pmcraid_allocate_control_blocks \- allocates memory control blocks
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pmcraid_allocate_control_blocks
.BI "(struct pmcraid_instance *pinstance "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pinstance" 12
pointer to per adapter instance structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates PCI memory for DMAable buffers like IOARCB, IOADLs
and IOASAs. This is called after command blocks are already allocated.

Return Value
0 in case it can allocate all control blocks, otherwise -ENOMEM
